WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();
driver.get("https://google.com");
-----------------
What Happens Internally
1️⃣ Test Script Execution

Automation script me jab driver.get("URL") run hota hai, to command Selenium Client Library ko send hoti hai.

2️⃣ Command Converted to HTTP Request

Selenium Client Library command ko W3C WebDriver Protocol request me convert karti hai.

Example request:

POST /session/{sessionId}/url
{
  "url": "https://google.com"
}
Request Sent to Browser Driver

Yeh request browser driver ko send hoti hai:

Chrome → ChromeDriver

Firefox → GeckoDriver

Edge → EdgeDriver

4️⃣ Browser Driver Communicates with Browser

Browser driver request ko browser ko forward karta hai.

Browser ko instruction milta hai:

➡️ Open the given URL

5️⃣ Browser Loads the Web Page

Browser:

URL open karta hai

Server ko request bhejta hai

Page resources load karta hai (HTML, CSS, JS)

6️⃣ Response Sent Back

Page load hone ke baad browser driver Selenium ko response send karta hai:

➡️ Page loaded successfully

Flow Summary
Test Script
     ↓
Selenium Client Library
     ↓
W3C WebDriver Protocol (HTTP request)
     ↓
Browser Driver (ChromeDriver)
     ↓
Browser opens URL
Interview Me Short Answer

Agar interviewer bole short me explain karo, to aise bolo:

When we run driver.get("URL"), Selenium sends a command through the client library using the W3C WebDriver protocol
to the browser driver such as ChromeDriver. 
The browser driver then instructs the browser to open the specified URL, and once the page is loaded, 
the response is sent back to the test script.
